                            <!--<p class="c1"><span class="c8">Lixi.Global Privacy Policy</span></p>-->
                            <p class="c1 c11"><span class="c4">Last updated: Dec. 28th, 2015</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c4">We at Lixi.Global know your privacy matters. This Privacy Policy covers how Lixi.Global uses the personal information we collect through the Lixi.Global Sites. In this Privacy Policy:</span></p><ul class="c18 lst-kix_list_1-0 start"><li class="c1 c12"><span class="c4">When we say&nbsp;</span><span class="c4 c19">“Lixi.Global”</span><span class="c4">, we mean Lixi.Global, Inc. (At times, we just refer to Lixi.Global as “we” and “us” - we hope this Privacy Policy reads better when we do that.)</span></li><li class="c1 c12"><span class="c4">When we say&nbsp;</span><span class="c4 c19">“Lixi.Global Sites”</span><span class="c4">&nbsp;or&nbsp;</span><span class="c4 c19">“Sites”</span><span class="c4">, we mean&nbsp;Lixi.Global&nbsp;and other official Lixi.Global websites and Lixi.Global apps that link to this Privacy Policy.</span></li></ul><p class="c1"><span class="c4">If you have any questions or comments about this Privacy Policy, or if you would like us to update information we have about you, please contact us at 3329 w Apollo Rd </span><span class="c20 c21"><a class="c13" href="mailto:privacy@Lixi.Global">privacy@Lixi.Global</a></span><span class="c4">&nbsp;or Lixi.Global.com, Inc., Attention: Privacy, 3329 W Apollo Rd Phoenix, AZ 85041.</span></p><p class="c1 c9"><span class="c2 c3"></span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c8">Information Collected</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">When You Provide Information Directly to Us</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2">When you visit the Lixi.Global Sites, you may provide personal information directly to us, including:</span></p><ul class="c18 lst-kix_list_2-0 start"><li class="c0"><span class="c2">Your contact information, and the receiver information such as name, address, telephone number, and email</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">Payment information, such as your credit card details, banking details, payment service details, and billing address</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">The receiver also needs to give shipping information and the shipping information to our third party service provider to ship your purchases to. </span></li></ul><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">When you use an external social network (for example, your Facebook account) to log in to the Lixi.Global Sites or to interact with Lixi.Global in another way, we may collect your name and other details from your social network profile and account (please see your social network’s privacy policy or support documents for more information about their sharing of information with connected accounts).</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">Information Collected by Automated Means</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">When you use the Lixi.Global Sites, we and third parties may collect certain information by automated means, using technologies such as cookies, Web server logs, Web beacons, JavaScript and components of our apps.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">Cookies</span></p><p class="c1 c9"><span class="c2 c10"></span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2">Cookies are files that websites send to your computer or other Internet-connected device to uniquely identify your browser or to store information or settings on your device. Our Sites may use HTTP cookies, HTML5 cookies, Flash cookies and other types of local storage (such as browser-based or plugin-based local storage). Your browser may tell you how to be notified when you receive certain types of cookies and how to restrict or disable certain cookies. You also may be able to delete your Flash cookies or adjust your Flash cookie settings by visiting the Adobe Flash Website Storage Settings Manager by following Adobe's instructions&nbsp;</span><span class="c16"><a class="c13" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.macromedia.com/support/documentation/en/flashplayer/help/settings_manager.html&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEwc-o2swCy42rCS0ECszqtBEAjiw">here</a></span><span class="c2">&nbsp;(instruction vary depending on your operating system and version of Flash).&nbsp;</span><span class="c2 c19">Please note, however, that without cookies you may not be able to use all of the features of our Sites.</span></p><p class="c1 c9"><span class="c2 c3"></span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">Web server logs and Web Beacons</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">In conjunction with the gathering of information through cookies, Web servers may log information such as your device type, operating system type, browser type, domain, and other system settings, as well as the language your system uses and the country and time zone where your device is located. The Web server logs also may record information such as the address of the Web page that referred you to our Sites and the IP address of the device you use to connect to the Internet. They also may log information about your interaction with our Sites, such as which pages you visit. To control which Web servers collect information by automated means, we may place tags on our Web pages called "Web beacons," which are files that link Web pages to particular Web servers and their cookies.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">JavaScript</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">We or third parties also may send instructions to your device using JavaScript or other computer languages to store or gather the sorts of information described above and other details about your interactions with the Sites.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">Our apps</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">Similar information may be collected through automated means by our apps, including unique device identifiers (such as advertising identifiers), geolocation information, IP address, device information, Internet connection information, as well as details about your device (such as device type), mobile browser or operating system, interactions with our apps and other technologies.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">How Information is Used</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">We may use the information you provide directly to us and information collected by automated means for various purposes, including to:</span></p><ul class="c18 lst-kix_list_3-0 start"><li class="c0"><span class="c2">Process, evaluate, and respond to your requests, inquiries, and applications</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">Create, administer, and communicate with you about your accounts</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">Contact you with marketing communications online and offline, including with respect to Lixi.Global’s products and services or those of our retail and marketing partners</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">Display relevant advertising to you on our Sites and across the Internet</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">Verify your identity</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">Operate, evaluate, and improve our business (including developing new products and services; managing our communications; performing market research, data analytics and data enhancement and insights; determining and managing the effectiveness of our advertising and marketing; analyzing, improving and customizing products, services, Sites and communications; administering our Sites; and performing accounting, auditing, billing, reconciliation, and collection activities)</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">Protect against and prevent fraud, unauthorized transactions, claims and other liabilities, and manage risk exposure and quality</span></li></ul><ul class="c18 lst-kix_list_5-0 start"><li class="c1 c12 c22"><span class="c2 c6">Comply with and enforce applicable legal requirements, industry standards and our policies and terms, such as our&nbsp;</span><span class="c5"><a class="c13" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.lixi.global/Terms-of-Use&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNG_gXlnmpdUpoVeBhktQL4qN3CxXg">Terms of Use</a></span></li></ul><p class="c1"><span class="c2">We use third-party Web analytics services on our Sites, such as those of Google Analytics. These service providers use cookies and other technology (as described in the "Information Collected by Automated Means" section above) to help us analyze how users use the Sites. The information collected by such technology (including, where applicable, your IP address) will be disclosed to or collected directly by these service providers. Learn about Google Analytics and its opt-out choices&nbsp;</span><span class="c15"><a class="c13" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNHjpkh29xEIs5fjFBmeFCTl9pEooA">here</a></span><span class="c16"><a class="c13" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNHjpkh29xEIs5fjFBmeFCTl9pEooA">.</a></span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2">Data about your activities on our Sites may be collected for use in providing advertising tailored to your individual interests on other websites and online services. You may choose whether to have your information collected for that purpose. We participate in advertising services administered by third parties. The ad services may track your online activities over time by collecting information through automated means, including through the use of the automated technologies described above, and they may use this information to show you advertisements for Lixi.Global or others that are tailored to your</span><span class="c2 c3">&nbsp;</span><span class="c2">individual interests or characteristics and/or based on prior visits to our Sites. We and third-party vendors may use first-party cookies and third-party cookies together, as well as other automated means and the data collected through such means, (1) to inform, optimize, and serve ads (including ads based on past visits to our Sites) and (2) to report on our ad impressions, other uses of ad services, and interactions with these ad impressions and ad services (including how they are related to visits to our Sites). To learn more about interest-based advertising generally, including how to opt out from the targeting of interest-based ads by some of our current ad service partners,&nbsp;</span><span class="c15"><a class="c13" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.aboutads.info/choices&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNG9ymLpw6z51I6DVBRnl_zNEQkKsg">click here</a></span><span class="c2">. You also may use your device settings to indicate certain preferences regarding the serving of advertisements based on your mobile device’s advertising identifier. For the most effective and up-to-date method of doing so on your particular device and operating system, you should consult your device settings and the instructions provided by your device manufacturer.</span></p><p class="c1 c9"><span class="c2 c3"></span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">Information Sharing</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">We share personal information we collect on our Sites with our service providers. We provide personal information to the merchants who fulfill the orders you place on our Sites. We share personal information with our subsidiaries, affiliates and joint marketing partners. We may share aggregated, anonymized or de-identified personal information with any third party, without any restriction, including through the use of cookies and other automated technologies. We may also share personal information at your request.</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">Subject to applicable law, we may disclose information about you (1) if we are required to do so by law, regulation or legal process, such as a subpoena; (2) when we believe disclosure would be appropriate in response to requests by government entities, such as law enforcement authorities; (3) when we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to prevent physical, financial or other harm, injury or loss; (4) in connection with an investigation of suspected or actual unlawful activity or (5) for fraud detection and prevention.</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">We also will transfer personal information we have about you in the event we sell or transfer all or a portion of our business or assets (such as in connection with a merger, acquisition, reorganization, dissolution or liquidation) or take steps in anticipation of such a transaction.</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">Third parties may collect personally identifiable information about your online activities over time and across different websites when you use our Sites. For example, third-party providers of certain embedded content and tools on our Sites (such as social network plug-ins) may collect personal information directly from you in connection with your interaction with such content and tools. Such providers’ use of the information is subject to their own privacy policies, which we recommend you</span><span class="c2 c3">&nbsp;</span><span class="c2">review. We are not responsible for such providers’ privacy practices, which are not covered by this Privacy Policy.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">Your Choices</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">If you would like to update or modify your personal information, you may contact us as described in the&nbsp;</span><span class="c2 c20">How To Contact Us</span><span class="c2">&nbsp;section below or, where applicable on certain Lixi.Global Sites, you may make these choices directly by logging into your account. You also may unsubscribe from any of our promotional emails by clicking on the “unsubscribe” link in any promotional email you receive from us.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">Information Security</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">Information security is something that we all have to work at to make e-commerce safer. We can’t promise that our security program will eliminate all security risks. We take reasonable steps to protect your information, but when you provide information to us (for example, payment card information), you do so at your own risk. You can do your part by taking steps such as:</span></p><ul class="c18 lst-kix_list_4-0 start"><li class="c0"><span class="c2">using a unique password for our Sites that never has or will be used anywhere else – please think up a new one that you never used before – and please only use that password with us</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">protecting the confidentiality of your username and password – don’t give your username and password to anyone, anywhere, anytime</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">accessing our Sites only from devices that have an up-to-date operating system and up-to-date security software (this makes the Lixi.Global Site work better anyway), and</span></li><li class="c0"><span class="c2">notifying us of any suspected unauthorized activity – you can contact us to try to help figure this out. We can take steps to help reset your account.</span></li></ul><p class="c1"><span class="c2">Taking these steps will not guarantee security but may help lower the risk or impact of certain security threats. For further information about protecting your security, visit&nbsp;</span><span class="c15"><a class="c13" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.consumer.ftc.gov/topics/computer-security&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNHPQQkeirgtVw4pt8Mjwhq-w3RkCw">http://www.consumer.ftc.gov/topics/computer-security</a></span><span class="c15">.</span></p><p class="c1 c9"><span class="c2"></span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">Links to Other Websites and Online Services</span></p><p class="c1 c11"><span class="c2">The Lixi.Global Sites may provide links to other websites and online services, such as for your convenience and for your information. For example, we may provide links to the websites of merchants or manufacturers of products sold on the Lixi.Global Sites or third party service providers that help the Lixi.Global Sites work well. Linked websites and services may have their own privacy policies, which we strongly suggest you review. We are not responsible for the content of any third-party websites or services, any use of those websites or services, or their privacy or security practices.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2 c10">Updates to Our Privacy Policy</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2">We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our personal information practices or relevant laws or, as a new company, as we grow and do cool new stuff. To notify you of any changes that we make, we will post the updated version on&nbsp;</span><span class="c15"><a class="c13" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.lixi.global/Terms-of-Use&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNE4cB9LNZ_0tMh970LymIvtDDd4og">www.Lixi.Global</a></span><span class="c2">&nbsp;and indicate at the top of the Privacy Policy when it was last updated.</span></p><p class="c1 c9"><span class="c2 c3"></span></p><p class="c1"><a name="h.gjdgxs"></a><span class="c2 c10">How to Contact Us</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c2">If you have any questions or comments about this Privacy Policy, or if you would like us to update information we have about you, please contact us at </span><span class="c14"><a class="c13" href="mailto:privacy@Lixi.Global">privacy@Lixi.Global</a></span><span class="c2">&nbsp;or Lixi.Global.com, Inc., Attention: Privacy, 3329 W Apollo Rd, Phoenix, AZ 85041.</span></p><p class="c1 c9"><span></span></p>
